  <front>
    <title>The Generalized TTL Security Mechanism (GTSM)</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-rtgwg-rfc3682bis-10"/>
    <author initials="C." surname="Pignataro" fullname="Carlos Pignataro"/>
    <author initials="P." surname="Savola" fullname="Pekka Savola"/>
    <author initials="D." surname="Meyer" fullname="David Meyer"/>
    <author initials="V." surname="Gill" fullname="Vijay Gill"/>
    <author initials="J." surname="Heasley" fullname="John Heasley"/>
    <date day="25" month="June" year="2007"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>The use of a packet's Time to Live (TTL) (IPv4) or Hop Limit (IPv6) to verify whether the packet was originated by an adjacent node on a connected link has been used in many recent protocols.  This document generalizes this technique.  This document obsoletes Experimental RFC 3682. [STANDARDS-TRACK]
	 </t>
    </abstract>
